Forty-three people died when a Tube train failed to stop at the Northern Line terminus, in what remains the worst peace-time accident on the London Underground. The cause of the crash has never been established. 101 years ago (1921) A rebellion began in the Soviet naval city of Kronstadt, near Petrograd, with sailors and citizens rising up against the country's newly established Bolshevik government. The rebels demanded the restoration of civil rights and greater economic freedom, but the revolt was brutally suppressed by the authorities. 56 years ago (1966) Chancellor James Callaghan confirmed in his Budget statement to the House of Commons the "historic and momentous" decision to switch to decimal currency.The change over to the decimal system - which was pioneered in the US in 1786 - would not happen for a further five years.